'''''Star Wreck''''' is a [[text adventure]] game written in 1987 by Charles A. Sharp. It was published by [[Alternative Software]] for the [[ZX Spectrum|Spectrum 48k]],<ref>[http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0007037 ''Star Wreck''] at World of Spectrum</ref> [[Amstrad CPC]],<ref>[http://www.cpczone.net/index.php?game=3014 ''Star Wreck''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927002113/http://www.cpczone.net/index.php?game=3014 |date=2007-09-27 }} at CPCZone.com</ref> and [[Commodore 64]].<ref>[http://www.gamebase64.com/game.php?id=7353&d=45 ''Star Wreck''] at Gamebase 64</ref> The game takes place in a parody of the ''[[Star Trek]]'' universe and the player takes on the role of Captain James T. Cake of the USS ''Paralysed''.
